{"type":"section","nativeType":"section","number":"1606","heading":"Subsequent impleader of dismissed biomaterials supplier","label":"1606 Subsequent impleader of dismissed biomaterials supplier","identifier":"/us/usc/t21/s1606","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t21/ch21","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft21%2Fs1606","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":["Statutory Notes and Related Subsidiaries","Effective DateSection applicable to all civil actions covered under this chapter commenced on or after , including any in which the harm or harmful conduct occurred before such date, see , set out as a note under .Aug. 13, 1998section 8 of Pub. L. 105–230section 1601 of this title"],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"subsection","nativeType":"subsection","number":"a","heading":"Impleading of dismissed defendant","label":"a Impleading of dismissed defendant","identifier":"/us/usc/t21/s1606/a","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t21/s1606","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft21%2Fs1606%2Fa","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"1","heading":null,"label":"1","identifier":"/us/usc/t21/s1606/a/1","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t21/s1606/a","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft21%2Fs1606%2Fa%2F1","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"A","heading":null,"label":"A","identifier":"/us/usc/t21/s1606/a/1/A","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t21/s1606/a/1","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft21%2Fs1606%2Fa%2F1%2FA","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"the negligence or intentionally tortious conduct of the dismissed supplier was an actual and proximate cause of the harm to the claimant; and","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"B","heading":null,"label":"B","identifier":"/us/usc/t21/s1606/a/1/B","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t21/s1606/a/1","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft21%2Fs1606%2Fa%2F1%2FB","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"the manufacturer’s liability for damages should be reduced in whole or in part because of such negligence or intentionally tortious conduct; or","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"2","heading":null,"label":"2","identifier":"/us/usc/t21/s1606/a/2","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t21/s1606/a","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft21%2Fs1606%2Fa%2F2","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"A","heading":null,"label":"A","identifier":"/us/usc/t21/s1606/a/2/A","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t21/s1606/a/2","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft21%2Fs1606%2Fa%2F2%2FA","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"the negligence or intentionally tortious conduct of the dismissed supplier was an actual and proximate cause of the harm to the claimant; and","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"B","heading":null,"label":"B","identifier":"/us/usc/t21/s1606/a/2/B","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t21/s1606/a/2","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft21%2Fs1606%2Fa%2F2%2FB","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"the claimant is unlikely to be able to recover the full amount of its damages from the remaining defendants.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]}]},{"type":"subsection","nativeType":"subsection","number":"b","heading":"Standard of liability","label":"b Standard of liability","identifier":"/us/usc/t21/s1606/b","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t21/s1606","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft21%2Fs1606%2Fb","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"1","heading":null,"label":"1","identifier":"/us/usc/t21/s1606/b/1","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t21/s1606/b","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft21%2Fs1606%2Fb%2F1","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"may, prior to entry of judgment on the claim against it, supplement the record of the proceeding that was developed prior to the grant of the motion for impleader under subsection (a); and","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"2","heading":null,"label":"2","identifier":"/us/usc/t21/s1606/b/2","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t21/s1606/b","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft21%2Fs1606%2Fb%2F2","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"may be found liable to a manufacturer or a claimant only to the extent required and permitted by any applicable State or Federal law other than this chapter.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]},{"type":"subsection","nativeType":"subsection","number":"c","heading":"Discovery","label":"c Discovery","identifier":"/us/usc/t21/s1606/c","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t21/s1606","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft21%2Fs1606%2Fc","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"Nothing in this section shall give a claimant or any other party the right to obtain discovery from a biomaterials supplier at any time prior to grant of a motion for impleader beyond that allowed under .section 1605 of this title","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]}
